{"build_type":"library","description":"Walk one loaded object's relocation array and push each relocation target's name onto the linker's explicit dependency-closure worklist buffer (state embedded: buf[0]=top, buf[1]=cap, buf[2..]=names). The relocations ARE the dependency list, so pushing their targets is how the transitive closure is discovered without native recursion. Self-tail-recursive over the reloc index (compiled to a jmp-back loop, O(1) native stack); replaces the former import-relocation-targets-inside-dependency-closure which recursed mutually into import-named-object. Fails hard (worklist_overflow) if the buffer would exceed capacity. Register-ABI clean: 4 parameters (buf, relocs, ri, nr). Already-loaded names are guarded on pop in the driver, not here.","module_name":"push-dependency-target-names-onto-import-worklist","package_name":"push-dependency-target-names-onto-import-worklist","function_definitions":{"push-dependency-target-names-onto-import-worklist":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"buf","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"relocs","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"ri","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"nr","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_target","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"target"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_of","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"worklist_overflow"},{"instruction_type":"